}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The codification of the laws in this chapter is not intended to alter the existing jurisdictional relationship of the Secretaries who administer those laws.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In paragraph (2)(A)(iii), the word “trade” is substituted for “commerce” for consistency in the chapter.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idf6d7744c-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idf6d7744d-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section 506 of the Merchant Marine Act, 1936, referred to in par. (8), is section 506 of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1936-06-29/ch858"},"text":"act June 29, 1936, ch. 858","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/49/1985"},"text":"49 Stat. 1985","children":[],"tail":", which is set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t46/s53101"},"text":"section 53101 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idf6d7744e-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2022—Par. (5)(A)(iii). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/263"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–263","children":[],"tail":" substituted “foreign or domestic trade of the United States” for “United States foreign, Great Lakes, noncontiguous domestic, or short sea transportation trade”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2018—Par. (5)(A)(iii). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/232/s3546/q/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–232, § 3546(q)(1)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “transportation trade or” for “transportation trade trade or”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Par. (7). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/232/s3546/q/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–232, § 3546(q)(3)","children":[],"tail":", struck out par. (7), as added by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/304/s8/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–304, § 8(c)","children":[],"tail":", which read as follows: “The term ‘United States foreign trade’ includes those areas in domestic trade in which a vessel built with a construction-differential subsidy is allowed to operate under the first sentence of section 506 of the Merchant Marine Act, 1936.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Pars. (8), (9). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/232/s3546/q/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–232, § 3546(q)(2)","children":[],"tail":", (4), added par. (8) and redesignated former par. (8) as (9)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2007—Par. (5)(A)(iii). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/140/s1122/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–140, § 1122(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “noncontiguous domestic, or short sea transportation trade” for “or noncontiguous domestic”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Par. (7). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/140/s1122/a/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–140, § 1122(a)(2)","children":[],"tail":", added par. (7) relating to short sea transportation trade."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idf6d7744f-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":nu